    {
      "id": "f5d5d88f_d50d38db",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "There is one filebeat ConfigMap for AAI. The name generated by common.log.configMap will be 'RELEASE-aai-filebeat'. The problem occurs when using common.log.volumes in AAI components as for filebeat-conf volume generated ConfigMap name will be 'RELEASE-aai-${component}-filebeat' (e.g. 'RELEASE-aai-graphadmin-filebeat'). This is needed to set valid name.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7705,
        "name": "Maciej Wereski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "m.wereski@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "maciey"
      },
      "updated": "2021-10-13 14:47:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ae97f5b8_dbb7abe5",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "69524127_877c5b58",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "oh OK\nbut global values are the same for everybody and are taken from \"main\" (a.k.a onap) values.\nso everything put here will be overriden by global values set in AAI and will be overidden by global values of ONAP and at the end by possible overrides from user\n\nSo, if you need a specific stuff for a particular (sub)component, you need to set it out of global part",
